==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: calciferous
<hw>cal*cif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧l*s⟦icr⟧f"⟦etil⟧r*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>calx</ets>, <ets>calcis</ets>, lime +
<ets>-ferous</ets>.]</ety> <def>Bearing, producing, or containing
calcite, or carbonate of lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Calciferous epoch</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>an
epoch in the American lower Silurian system, immediately succeeding the
Cambrian period. The name alludes to the peculiar mixture of calcareous
and siliceous characteristics in many of the beds. See the Diagram under
<er>Geology</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calcific</ent>⟦br⟧
